On the other hand, does anyone doubt that Dynegy's acquisition of Enron with
PGE would necessitate a 511 filing to exercise influence?  The NW Natural
acquisition is not a done deal (the application hasn't even been filed).  So
does Dynegy assume that approval or does it prepare an application of its
own?  That would be a first: two simultaneous 511 applications over the same
company.  I would be real envious of PGE (not one, but two suitors) if I
wasn't married (and unable to buy stock in the company).
