>Marc, good question.  I think that Dynegy should want the NWN/PGE
>transaction to go forward quickly, for a couple reasons.  First, Dynegy
>ownes Illinova.  If Dynegy closed the Enron purchase prior to Enron
>completing the sale of PGE to NWN, then Dynegy would probably have pretty
>big SEC issues under PUHCA.  Also, I understand that yesterday, the credit
>ratings agencies were contemplating a downrating of Dynegy debt due to
>Dynegy's propspective debt load with Enron.  Dynegy was urged to complete
>all of Enron's asset sales so it could restore its balance sheet and
>maintain investment grade ratings.
>
>I'm not entirely sure, but suspect that all parties will want PGE to close
>first before the Dynegy/Enron closure.  Don't know if that helps.  If I
hear
>more, I'll let you know.  SKA
>
